<div id="empty_slate_system_roles" class="empty_slate">
  <h3>{lang}About JavaScript{/lang}</h3>
  
  <ul class="icon_list">
    <li>
      <img src="{image_url name=admin/modules.gif}" class="icon_list_icon" alt="" />
      <span class="icon_list_title">{lang}JavaScript is a System Requirement{/lang}</span>
      <span class="icon_list_description">{lang}Some system features such are Upload Files or Move to Trash require JavaScript to work properly. Because of that, JavaScript is a system requirement and it should be enabled in your browser for all system functions to work properly. Instructions for enabling JavaScript in supported browsers are provided below{/lang}:</span>
    </li>
    
    <li>
      <img src="{image_url name=browsers/ie.gif}" class="icon_list_icon" alt="" />
      <span class="icon_list_title">{lang}Enabling JavaScript in Microsoft Internet Explorer{/lang}</span>
      <span class="icon_list_description">
        {lang}To enable JavaScript support in Internet Explorer{/lang}:
        <ol>
          <li>{lang}Open <strong>Tools</strong> menu and select <strong>Internet Options</strong>{/lang}</li>
          <li>{lang}Click on <strong>Security</strong> tab and then on <strong>Custom Level...</strong> button{/lang}</li>
          <li>{lang}Scroll down until you find <strong>Scripting</strong> section. Set <strong>Active Scripting</strong> to Enabled and click OK{/lang}</li>
        </ol>
        <p class="center"><img src="{image_url name=browsers/ie-enable-js.gif}" alt="" /></p>
      </span>
    </li>
    
    <li>
      <img src="{image_url name=browsers/firefox.gif}" class="icon_list_icon" alt="" />
      <span class="icon_list_title">{lang}Enabling JavaScript in Mozilla Firefox{/lang}</span>
      <span class="icon_list_description">
        {lang}To enable JavaScript support in Firefox{/lang}:
        <ol>
          <li>{lang}Open <strong>Firefox</strong> menu and select <strong>Preferences</strong>{/lang}</li>
          <li>{lang}Click on <strong>Content</strong> tab{/lang}</li>
          <li>{lang}Make sure that <strong>Enable JavaScript</strong> option is checked{/lang}</li>
        </ol>
        <p class="center"><img src="{image_url name=browsers/firefox-enable-js.gif}" alt="" /></p>
      </span>
    </li>
    
    <li>
      <img src="{image_url name=browsers/safari.gif}" class="icon_list_icon" alt="" />
      <span class="icon_list_title">{lang}Enabling JavaScript in Apple Safari{/lang}</span>
      <span class="icon_list_description">
        {lang}To enable JavaScript support in Safari{/lang}:
        <ol>
          <li>{lang}Open <strong>Safari</strong> menu and select <strong>Preferences</strong>{/lang}</li>
          <li>{lang}Click on <strong>Security</strong> tab{/lang}</li>
          <li>{lang}Make sure that <strong>Enable JavaScript</strong> option is checked in Web content section{/lang}</li>
        </ol>
        <p class="center"><img src="{image_url name=browsers/safari-enable-js.gif}" alt="" /></p>
      </span>
    </li>
  </ul>
</div>